│                                                                                            │
│ ### 3. Root Cause Analysis                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ 1.  The Loop Vectorizer analyzes `loop.2` and needs to determine its trip count.           │
│ ScalarEvolution identifies the trip count as being related to the value of `%iv.1`.        │
│ 2.  From the perspective of `loop.2`, `%iv.1` is a `SCEVUnknown`. To get a concrete        │
│ `Value*` for it at the correct program point (the preheader of `loop.2`), the              │
│ `SCEVExpander` must determine the value of `%iv.1` after `loop.1` exits.                   │
│ 3.  The expander calls `getPHIValueAfterLoop()` to handle this. This function correctly    │
